Package: shinyDTC
Type: Package
Title: Simple Dynamic Timer Control
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
  person("Sigbert", "Klinke", email="sigbert@hu-berlin.de", role=c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A dynamic timer control is a Shiny widget that enables time-based processes in applications. 
    It allows users to execute these processes manually in individual steps or at customizable speeds. 
    The timer can be paused, resumed, or restarted. This control is particularly well-suited for simulations, 
    animations, countdowns, or interactive visualizations.
